Source: multicorn
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), dh-python, postgresql-all (>= 217~), postgresql-server-dev-all (>= 217~), python3-dev, python3-setuptools
Standards-Version: 4.7.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/pgsql-io/multicorn2

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-multicorn
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-multicorn
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, python3-multicorn (= ${binary:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Breaks: ${postgresql:Breaks}
Description: Python Foreign Data Wrapper framework for PostgreSQL
 Multicorn is a PostgreSQL extension that lets developers implement Foreign
 Data Wrappers in Python.
 .
 This package contains the PostgreSQL PGVERSION extension library and SQL files.

Package: python3-multicorn
Section: python
Architecture: any
Depends: ${python3:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Suggests: python3-docutils, python3-imapclient, python3-ldap3, python3-lxml, python3-psutil, python3-sqlalchemy
Description: Python modules for the Multicorn PostgreSQL extension
 Multicorn is a PostgreSQL extension that lets developers implement Foreign
 Data Wrappers in Python.
 .
 This package contains the shared Python 3 modules used by all PostgreSQL
 versions of the Multicorn extension.
